message: User: what are the entrace requirements for MScAC; Jonathan: The 2023 MScAC admission requirements typically include a four-year undergraduate degree in computer science or a related field, a minimum GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale, strong letters of recommendation, a statement of purpose, and GRE scores (optional). Additionally, applicants may be required to demonstrate proficiency in programming languages such as Java, Python, or C++.

User: what courses can I take?; Jonathan: You can take courses within the MScAC program, as well as courses from other departments such as Aerospace Engineering, Cell & Systems Biology, Computer Science, Ecology and Evolutionary Biology, Electrical & Computer Engineering, Mathematics, MHI courses, Molecular Genetics, Statistical Sciences, and Physics. You may need permission from the respective department through their Graduate Administrator to take courses outside of Computer Science. It is recommended to participate in departmental and MScAC academic activities, such as seminars, to stay updated on the latest research and meet professors, industry partners, and other graduate students. If you wish to change your concentration, you can submit a request with supporting rationale to the Associate Director, MScAC Administration for consideration.

User: What are the qualifications needed from India?; Jonathan: Applicants from India must have completed or be in the process of completing an appropriate undergraduate degree for the concentration they are applying to. They must have a standing equivalent to at least B+ (U of T 77-79%) in their final year of study. Additionally, they must achieve English-language proficiency according to the requirements set by the School of Graduate Studies. Work experience and research experience are preferred but not required. Applicants must also submit the required documents, including academic transcripts, resume/CV, program-specific questions, details of referees, English Language Proficiency (ELP) test scores, GRE scores (if applicable), and any other relevant information.

User: is there financial support for mscac students?; Jonathan: Yes, there are various options for financial support available to MScAC students, including government loans like OSAP, Teaching Assistantship positions, and consultation with a Financial Advisor at the School of Graduate Studies for budgeting assistance and information on bursaries, grants, loans, or other financial aid options. Students with certain major awards or loans that cover the Minimum Required Payment may also be able to defer their fees.
